		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Chinese remainder theorem</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>Chinese remainder theorem</b> is a result about <a href="/wiki/Modular_arithmetic" title="Modular arithmetic">congruences</a> in <a href="/wiki/Number_theory" title="Number theory">number theory</a> and its generalizations in <a href="/wiki/Abstract_algebra" title="Abstract algebra">abstract algebra</a>.</p>
